The paper focuses on deep neural networks for visual pattern classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses a specific technique for training classifiers with augmented data, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and multilayer perceptron (MLP) models, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the models on datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision (cs.CL).
